<paragraph id="725E36EC2451BD08FF66D83F1807A430" blockId="79.[151,1437,1661,1919]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FF66D83F1A80A596" bold="true" box="[198,447,1661,1687]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2451BD08FE1FD83F19A9A596" authorityName="Grayum &amp; de Nevers in de Nevers &amp; Grayum" authorityYear="1998" box="[447,662,1661,1687]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hugonis">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FE1FD83F19A9A596" box="[447,662,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Geonoma hugonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of a group of four Central American species, part of the 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2451BD08FF63D8E61A7FA5BF" authorityName="Wendland ex Spruce" authorityYear="1871" box="[195,320,1700,1726]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuneata">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FF63D8E61A7FA5BF" box="[195,320,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">G. cuneata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade, also including 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2451BD08FDE4D8E619FDA5BF" authorityName="Grayum" authorityYear="1998" box="[580,706,1700,1726]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FDE4D8E619FDA5BF" box="[580,706,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">G. brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FD72D8E618B6A5BF" box="[722,905,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2451BD08FD72D8E618BAA5BF" authorityName="de Nevers in de Nevers &amp; Grayum" authorityYear="1998" box="[722,901,1700,1726]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monospatha">G. monospatha</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2451BD08FC64D8E61F65A5BF" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1980" box="[964,1114,1700,1726]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="epetiolata">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FC64D8E61F65A5BF" box="[964,1114,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">G. epetiolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They all have unbranched or few-branched inflorescences and share the character state of the staminodial tubes being lobed at the apex, but the lobes are not spreading at anthesis and are not acuminate. 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2451BD08FC34D8B31F55A40A" authorityName="Grayum &amp; de Nevers in de Nevers &amp; Grayum" authorityYear="1998" box="[916,1130,1777,1803]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hugonis">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FC34D8B31F55A40A" box="[916,1130,1777,1803]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Geonoma hugonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from these species in its internodes covered with reddish or brownish scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2451BD08FF66D97C18F6A47E" blockId="79.[151,1437,1661,1919]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2451BD08FF66D97C1AC5A459" bold="true" box="[198,506,1854,1880]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
Only one trait (stem branching) varies in this species. There is geographic disjunction but this is likely to be an artifact of insufficient collecting.
</paragraph>
